images.description:
This little lady, my roommate found over 2 days down at our bin area of our apartment complex. The local kids said their uncle had her, then an Aunt. Poor love was alone & in heat. I told him to bring her up (not ever meeting her). She is the softest, gentle baby, I fell in love instantly (I’m not much a cat person). She sheds like crazy, her litter stanks, but I love her to bits, she’ll come up n perch with me like this from time to time for chin, chest, and belly rubs. I just can’t believe how gentle she is AND potty trained, instantly she knew where to go (in the bathroom).
I’m so lucky!!! Had to share.
Still no name, what do you loves think we should name her?? x

comment.comment: The stinky poo is going to be all the garbage she was eating to survive. I know it sounds bizarre but some kitten food will help with missing nutrients. She might need a dewormer too. I second the suggestion of Binny.
